<doc>
  <member name="PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE">
    <summary>
      <para>Describes the condition type to use when displaying the property in the query builder UI in Windows Vista, but not in Windows 7 and later.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>The flags in PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE affected the query string display in the <b>Advanced Query Builder</b> user interface in Windows Vista. In Windows 7 and later, the flags in PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE are not used.</para>
    </remarks>
  </member>
  <member name="PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE.PDCOT_NONE">
    <summary>
      <para>The default value; it means the condition type is unspecified.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE.PDCOT_STRING">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the string condition type.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE.PDCOT_SIZE">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the size condition type.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE.PDCOT_DATETIME">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the date/time condition type.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE.PDCOT_BOOLEAN">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the Boolean condition type.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="PROPDESC_CONDITION_TYPE.PDCOT_NUMBER">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the number condition type.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>